definition.value: *Epinephelus marginatus* (dusky grouper, merou) is the best known grouper of the Mediterranean Sea and North Africa coast. [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epinephelus_marginatus]

*Vaccinium parvifolium* (Red Huckleberry) is a species of *Vaccinium* native to the Pacific Northwest of North America. Indigenous peoples found the plant and its fruit very useful. The bright red, acidic berries were used extensively for food throughout the year.
Vaccinium reticulatum, known as ʻōhelo ʻai in Hawaiian, is a species of flowering plant in the heather family, Ericaceae, that is endemic to Hawaii.

*Lithospermum arvense*, the field gromwell, corn gromwell, or bastard alkanet, is a flowering plant of the family *Boraginaceae*. It is also known as *Buglossoides arvensis*. The European Union has granted the refined oil of the seed of *Buglossoides arvensis* novel food status and some farmers are growing it. [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lithospermum_arvense]

*Cordia myxa* is a species of flowering plant in the borage family, Boraginaceae. It is a medium-sized broad-leaved deciduous tree. Common names include Assyrian plum, lasura, pidar, panugeri, naruvilli, geduri, spistan, burgund dulu wanan and ntege.[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cordia_myxa]
